From 0baf5efbd5011ba31cbadb1a060b025443a344b0 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ketan Patil <ketanp@nvidia.com>
Date: Tue, 18 Jun 2024 06:13:47 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 56/95] NVIDIA: SAUCE: memory: Add support for T264 mc-err

Add support for mc-err logging for T264 in upstream mc driver.
- Add mc-error handling flow for MCF, HUB, HUBC, SBS and MC Channel.
- Each of these components have different interrupt lines for mc-err.
- Register interrupt handlers for interrupts from these different MSS
components.
- Introduce new SOC specific fields in tegra_mc_soc.

http://nvbugs/4655916

Upstream-Status: Backport
Signed-off-by: Ketan Patil <ketanp@nvidia.com>
Signed-off-by: Laxman Dewangan <ldewangan@nvidia.com>
Acked-by: Noah Wager <noah.wager@canonical.com>
Acked-by: Jacob Martin <jacob.martin@canonical.com>
Signed-off-by: Noah Wager <noah.wager@canonical.com>
(cherry picked from commit 4ef740cae9a684625284b6f255197a6f4ac02ac7)
Signed-off-by: Matt Madison <matt@madison.systems>
